description.narrative: UNICEF strengthened the national education system through evidence-based planning, policy dialogue, and technical assistance. In 2021, UNICEF became the coordinating agency, on behalf of the Ministry of Education and Technical Education (MoETE), for the Education Sector Analysis (ESA) and Education Sector Plan (ESP); forming and co-chairing the Local Education Group (LEG) and leading the ESA to completion. UNICEF continued to support the rollout of the reform, focusing on delivering quality learning to marginalized children through Pre-Primary Inclusive Education and Community-based Education (CBE). The UNICEF-led real-time monitoring assessment facilitated understanding of the impacts of COVID-19 on learning and informed programming decisions. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:29/12/2021
